    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for ascending series or flights of steps; utility constructions using steps and designed to bridge a vertical distance. A stairs is a construction or contrivance comprising a change of elevation consisting of one or more risers, as defined by the International Code Council.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
